The paper proposes a fast approximate message-passing algorithm for solving compressed sensing recovery problems with 1D-finite-difference sparsity in terms of MMSE estimation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a Bernoulli-Gaussian prior, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and the paper proposes an EM-tuning methodology, which is a common technique in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of convergence speed and CPU runtime, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
